{title: Give Me My Flowers While I'm Living}
{artist: Earl Scruggs and Lester Flatt}
{composer: Written by Louise Certain, Gladys Stacey, Elvin Bigger}

Recorded by Lester Flatt and Earl Scruggs
Written by Louise Certain, Gladys Stacey, Elvin Bigger
[C]In this world today while we're [G7]living
Some folks say the worst of us they [C]can
But when we are dead and in our [F]caskets
They [C]always slip some [G7]lilies in your [C]hand
Won't you give me my flowers while I'm [G7]living
And let me enjoy them while I [C]can
Please don't wait till I'm ready to be [F]buried
And [C]then slip some [G7]lilies in my [C]hand
In this world is where we need our [G7]flowers
A kind word to help us get [C]along
If you can't give me flowers while I'm [F]living
Then [C]please don't [G7]throw them when I'm [C]gone
Repeat #2